---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Card from '../../components/ui/Card.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/ui/CodeBlock.astro';
import { formatBinary } from '../../utils/formatters';
---

<Layout title="Data Representation - IG Computer Science">
  <h1>Data Representation</h1>
  
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2>Binary Numbers</h2>
    <p>
      Binary is a base-2 number system used by computers. It consists of only two digits: 0 and 1.
      Each digit in a binary number is called a bit (binary digit).
    </p>
    <Card title="Converting Binary to Decimal">
      <p>
        To convert binary to decimal, multiply each digit by its position value (power of 2) and sum the results.
      </p>
      <CodeBlock code={`Example: ${formatBinary('1101')}₂
1×2³ + 1×2² + 0×2¹ + 1×2⁰
8 + 4 + 0 + 1 = 13₁₀`} />
    </Card>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2>Hexadecimal</h2>
    <p>
      Hexadecimal is a base-16 number system. It uses digits 0-9 and letters A-F to represent values.
      It's often used as a more readable way to represent binary numbers.
    </p>
    <Card title="Hex to Binary Conversion">
      <p>Each hexadecimal digit represents exactly 4 binary digits:</p>
      <CodeBlock code={`A₁₆ = ${formatBinary('1010')}₂
F₁₆ = ${formatBinary('1111')}₂
Example: 2F₁₆ = ${formatBinary('00101111')}₂`} />
    </Card>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2>Text Representation</h2>
    <p>
      Computers store text using character encoding systems. ASCII and Unicode are two common encoding systems.
    </p>
    <Card title="ASCII">
      <p>
        ASCII uses 7 bits to represent characters, allowing for 128 different characters.
        Extended ASCII uses 8 bits, allowing for 256 characters.
      </p>
    </Card>
  </section>
</Layout>